## Event Colors

Events are color-coded by project for easy identification. Each campaign has a consistent color generated from a palette including:

- Blue, Red, Emerald, Amber, Violet
- Cyan, Lime, Pink, Indigo, Teal

This helps you quickly identify which project a follow-up belongs to when viewing multiple projects.

## Navigation

### Clicking Events

Click on any event to navigate directly to the address detail page. The link includes the project ID for proper context:

`https://sellfaster.eu/home/addresses/[addressSlug]?projectId=[projectId]`

From there you can:

- View full lead information
- Record a new interaction
- Record a sale
- See interaction history

## Empty State

If no follow-ups are scheduled, the calendar displays:
"No follow-ups scheduled"

This means you don't have any upcoming follow-up dates from interactions.

## Data Sources

The calendar displays follow-ups from:

- All team accounts you're a member of
- Interactions where a follow-up date was set
- Future follow-ups only (today and onwards)

## Creating Follow-Ups

To add events to your calendar:

1. Go to an lead detail page
1. Click **Add Interaction**
1. Enable the follow-up option
1. Set the date and time
1. Save the interaction

The follow-up appears on your calendar automatically.

> **Note:** Follow-ups cannot be created directly from the calendar. They must be created through interactions on address detail pages.

See [Follow-Up Reminders](/docs/user-guide/how-to/follow-up-reminders) for detailed instructions.

## Mobile Viewing

The calendar is responsive and works on mobile devices:

- Scroll horizontally to see the full week
- Tap events to navigate to address details
- Full-height display for maximum visibility

